# Hoosat Miningcore Frontend

This is source available miningcore frontend originally designed to work with Elva miningcore implementation.

## NGINX Configuration

Here is example of http configuration for NGINX. The miningcore frontend is SPA (single page application) and requires to route every non-existent route to `index.html`, because there is no backend code to reply into HTTP queris like `

```
server {
    listen 80;
    server_name your-domain.com;  # Replace with your domain or IP address

    root /path/to/your/spa/build;  # Replace with the path to your built Miningcore Frontend
    index index.html;

    location / {
        try_files $uri $uri/ /index.html;  # If the requested file doesn't exist, serve index.html
    }
}
```

## Adding Coin Data for the Frontend

The `src/listed-coins.js` file contains the data for the coins listed in the pool. Each coin entry includes essential details such as wallet addresses, transaction links, and stratum information. For example:

```javascript
{
  coin: "BTC",
  prefix: ["1", "3", "bc1"],
  wallet: "https://www.blockchain.com/btc/address/",
  transaction: "https://www.blockchain.com/btc/tx/",
  blocks: "https://www.blockchain.com/btc/block/",
  stratum: [{ location: "Global", domain: "stratum+tcp://btc.pool.com" }],
}
```

To add a new coin to the pool, include it in `listed-coins.js` with the appropriate stratum details. You can also add extra coin information, but only the coins found through the API will be displayed on the frontend.

## Adding coin icons to the Frontend

You can add `.png` icon to `img/icon` and convert them with `convert.bash` into `img/webp` or you can add `.webp` directly to `img/webp`.

## Strings to replace

There are few strings you need to replace.

- DOMAIN_ADDDRESS_HERE
- EMAIL_ADDRESS_HERE
- DISCORD_LINK_HERE
- TELEGRAM_LINK_HERE
- COMPANY_NAME_HERE

If you have permission from Hoosat Oy you can replace the copyright.

